  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>When you hit a creature with a melee weapon attack, you can spend 1 force point to use a Force-Empowered Self effect. You have three such effects: Deflection, Double Strike, and Slow Time. You can only use each effect once per turn, and you can only use one effect per hit.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Deflection.</em></strong> You can roll a [[/r d4]] and add it to your AC against one attack before the start of your next turn.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Double Strike.</em></strong> You can roll a [[/r d4]] and deal additional damage of the same type equal to the amount rolled.</p>\n<p><strong><em>Slow Time.</em></strong> You can roll a [[/r d4]] to increase your speed by 5 x the amount rolled until the end of your turn.</p>\n<p>You can only spend a number of force points in this way equal to your proficiency bonus. You regain the ability to do so when you complete a long rest.</p>",
